This paper deals with the task of text-to-speech conversion, which is a natural language processing (NLP) task. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of statistical models and neural networks, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions the importance of fast inference for deployment on devices with restricted resources, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.SD (Sound). Finally, the paper proposes a new decoder network architecture, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Learning) a possible sub-category.
